descript.abstract: World Cities represents the locations of major cities of the world.
descript.purpose: World Cities provides a base map layer of the cities for the world. The cities include national capitals, provincial capitals, major population centers, and landmark cities.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:15,000,000.

digtinfo.formspec: The SHP file contains the geospatial data. The SHX file contains the index of the geospatial data. The DBF file contains the attribute data in dBASE® format. The PRJ file contains the coordinate system information (optional). The AVL file contains the legend information (optional). The SBN and SBX files contain the spatial index of the geospatial data (optional). The XML file (*.shp.xml) contains the metadata describing the data set (optional).

procstep.procdesc:
The following steps were performed by ESRI for Data & Maps 2002: Moved Mangyshlak to its correct location. Updated Fips_cntry and Cntry_name attributes for East Timor, Yugoslavia and their capitals. Created ArcGIS™ layer file (.lyr) and ArcView legend file (.avl). Copied projection file (.prj) and created spatial indices.
The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the features from ArcWorld Supplement. Updated by adding/deleting features and changing attribute values, based on political changes and other factors. Created ArcGIS™ layer file (.lyr). Created ArcView legend file (.avl). Created projection file (.prj). Created spatial indices.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Added one city each to West Bank and Gaza Strip. Added or recorded provincial capitals for South Africa. Corrected spellings of two cities. Changed Yugoslavia to Serbia and Montenegro. Created ArcView legend file (.avl), ArcGIS™ layer file (.lyr) file, projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was extracted from the ArcWorld Supplement database. No detailed evaluation of the positional accuracy of the ArcWorld Supplement data has been made; knowledge of the source World Data Bank II (WDBII) data is insufficient to determine positional accuracy of data derived from the source.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is created directly from a topologically correct ArcInfo™ coverage.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
